# Git remote: dirnbauer only

This workspace is **`dirnbauer/typo3-mcp-server`**. Do not use or push to **`hauptsacheNet/typo3-mcp-server`**.

## Git

- **Push only to `origin`** → `https://github.com/dirnbauer/typo3-mcp-server.git`
- Never run `git push upstream`, `git push hauptsacheNet`, or any push targeting `hauptsacheNet/typo3-mcp-server`
- If an `upstream` remote exists, treat it as read-only context only; never push to it

## GitHub CLI (`gh`)

`gh` may default to `hauptsacheNet/typo3-mcp-server` in this clone. Always pass the repo explicitly:

```bash
gh run list --repo dirnbauer/typo3-mcp-server
gh pr create --repo dirnbauer/typo3-mcp-server
gh run watch <id> --repo dirnbauer/typo3-mcp-server
```

Never use `--repo hauptsacheNet/typo3-mcp-server` and never create PRs or push commits on that remote.

## CI and releases

When checking Actions, opening PRs, or reporting CI URLs, use:

`https://github.com/dirnbauer/typo3-mcp-server`
